=== BE6500 (0bda:8912) on Raspberry Pi 5 -- morrownr rtw89_8922au_git ===
Date: Sun Apr 12 2026
Kernel: 6.12.47+rpt-rpi-2712 (Pi OS stock)
Chipset: RTL8922AU (WiFi 7 / 802.11be)

USB ENUMERATION: Bus 4 Port 1, 5000 Mbps (USB 3.0 SuperSpeed)
Switch-mode SUCCESSFUL on aarch64 + Broadcom RP1 xHCI for the WiFi 7 chipset

WIFI LINK:
  5 GHz (5500 MHz), EHT (WiFi 7) negotiated
  Signal: -34 dBm
  rx bitrate: 1020.6 Mbit/s (EHT-MCS 10, NSS 2)
  tx bitrate: 1296.7 Mbit/s (EHT-MCS 12, NSS 2)

IPERF3 UPLOAD (30s): 774 Mbit/sec, 2.70 GB, 0 retransmits
IPERF3 DOWNLOAD (30s): 261 Mbit/sec, 934 MB (lower than Framework, likely
  Pi CPU bottleneck on RX processing)

SIGNIFICANCE:
  WiFi 7 (EHT) on a $80 single-board computer via USB adapter. Demonstrates
  that Bitterblue's switch-mode code enables the latest WiFi standard on
  ARM platforms that have no stock kernel driver for this chip at all.
